  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Engineer (ACMV)",
  "description": "<p><u>Job Responsibilities</u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Experience in managing construction work regarding ACMV inclusive of heat source equipment (chiller, etc), air conditioning equipment &amp; ventilation equipment.</li>\n  <li>Experience in executing work on large project (Contract amount more than SGD 10 million) with 100 to 200 workers at peak period daily.</li>\n  <li>Works &amp; coordinates closely with main contractor, clients, consultants on technical matters.</li>\n  <li>Provides guidance to engineers &amp; supervisors in relation to site work.</li>\n  <li>Supervises &amp; coordinates ACMV services work &amp; works closely with other department staff to meet project timelines.</li>\n  <li>Manages procurement (the submission of materials, samples &amp; work progress.</li>\n  <li>Manages the submission of method statements &amp; work progress.</li>\n  <li>Ensures quality of work is achieved &amp; safety regulations are compiled with.</li>\n  <li>Manages the submission of shop drawings &amp; work progress.</li>\n  <li>Coordinates/discuss with suppliers to prepare the manufacture drawings.</li>\n  <li>Checks the manufacture drawings whether it is compiled as discussed with suppliers &amp; whether it is compiled with contract (specification) &amp; the comments given by the client, consultant &amp; owner.</li>\n  <li>Attends meetings &amp; discussions with main contractor.</li>\n  <li>To be the point of contact for giving &amp; receiving instructions, documents, etc to &amp; from client, customers.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Job Requirements</u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least a Bachelor Degree in Mechanical Engineering.</li>\n  <li>At least 15 to 25 years of relevant working experience.</li>\n  <li>Preferably with managerial experience managing a department before.</li>\n  <li>Must be willing to work in Tuas area. Company transport from MRT station will be provided.</li>\n  <li>Able to handle stress from main contractor.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>",
